    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Just one week after a Russian general proclaimed the war in Chechnya all but won, a series of bombings killed at least 33 Russian troops in the breakaway republic.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Just one week after a Russian general proclaimed the war in Chechnya all but won, a series of bombings killed at least 33 Russian troops in the breakaway republic.</p>
        <p>The truck bomb attacks, which occurred on Sunday night, took place in towns and cities supposedly under Russian control. President Vladimir Putin promised to curtail the role in Chechnya of Russian police -- whose troops were killed in the bombings. The police came from throughout Russia and their deaths have sent shock waves through the nation.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL R. GORDON</p>
        <p>JULY 2-8</p>
      </block>
